    Black Aracnia looked at the body of Darkmouse. It had been dead for 
several hours. Aracnia was mournful because Darkmouse was a great soldier, if 
not, in some strange and morbid way, her only friend left after the departure 
of Hell Beast and her old crew.
    In the lab, Hell Beasts old lab, Aracnia hoped to bring Darkmouse back to 
life. He left a large amount of Liquid Energon behinde and Aracnia tended to 
drain her mech and replace it with the powerful fluid. If it worked, 
Darkmouse would be very energenic. She would most likely have a boost in 
strength, size, and intelligence. It was risky, but she needed Darkmouse.
    Alone, with the body, Aracnia inserted one tube into her left arm that 
would pump out the Mech, and placed a tube in her right arm that would pump 
in the Liquid Energon. In any even, they would know if she would rise agian 
in an hour or so.
